i18n.CAP.type_helper: Indicates whether the request is for home collection or a posting authorization. CA = Home collect. If there is no home collect in the locality, the system automatically transforms the order into a posting authorization. C = Home collect. If there is no collect at the indicated location, the system does not process the request. A = Posting Authorization If no value is passed in this tag, the system understands that it is a post authorization request.
i18n.CAP.capnumero: Posting Authorization Code (when customer already has)
i18n.CAP.capnumero_helper: Posting Authorization Number. Used when the customer already has a numerical range for this type of request
i18n.CAP.ag_helper: Home collection: Date to schedule the collection. If informed, the order is retained in the system and the first collection attempt is only made on the informed date. The system only accepts dates with more than five calendar days from the date of processing the order. Posting Authorization: Indicates the number of days the authorization is valid. The validity must be at least 5 and at most 90 days. If not informed, the validity of the authorization will be 10 (ten) calendar days from the date of processing the order.
